Usage: cutRectilinearInst [-help] -inst <inst|hInst|group>+ [-pushOut <string>] {{-refInst <inst|hInst|group>+ [-spacingX <float>] [-spacingY <float>]} | {-corner <string> [-x <float> -y <float>]} | {-cutBox {x1 y1 x2 y2}}}

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-corner <string>              # name of a corner (string, optional)
-cutBox {x1 y1 x2 y2}         # rectilinear box that is to be cut
                              # (box, optional)
-inst <inst|hInst|group>+     # name of a hierarchical instance
                              # ((inst|hInst|group)+, required)
-pushOut <string>             # name of a side or edge (string, optional)
-refInst <inst|hInst|group>+  # name of a referenced instance
                              # ((inst|hInst|group)+, required)
-spacingX <float>             # X (float, optional)
-spacingY <float>             # Y (float, optional)
-x <float>                    # x offset value (float, optional)
-y <float>                    # y offset value (float, optional)